id="v.iii.i-p1.1"></span>Two Epistles Concerning Virginity.</span>

<span id="v.iii.i-p2"></span> ————————————

<span id="v.iii.i-p3"></span><span class="c6"><span
id="v.iii.i-p3.1"></span>The First Epistle of the Blessed Clement, the
Disciple of Peter the Apostle.</span>

<span id="v.iii.i-p4"></span><span class="c1"><span
id="v.iii.i-p4.1"></span>Chapter I.—The Salutation.</span>

<span id="v.iii.i-p5"></span><span class="c9"><span
id="v.iii.i-p5.1"></span>To</span> all those who love and cherish their
life *which is* in Christ through God the Father, and obey the truth of
God in hope of eternal life; to those who bear affection towards their
brethren and towards their neighbours in the love of God; to the blessed
*brother* virgins, <span id="fr_291"></span>[292](#fn_291.md) who devote
themselves to preserve virginity “for the sake of the kingdom of
heaven;” <span id="fr_292"></span>[293](#fn_292.md) and to the holy
*sister* virgins:  the peace which is in God. <span
id="fr_293"></span>[294](#fn_293.md)

